# ==============================================================================
# Entity Linking Notes
# ==============================================================================

# Surface forms "Dave", "DAVE", "Santan Dave" all refer to the same artist.
# The ontology has no Artist/Performer class, so this cannot be represented.
# See GAPS section below.

# "Washington, DC" → linked to mv:WashingtonDC (ontology individual)
# "Berlin, Germany" → linked to mv:Berlin (ontology individual)
# "Paris, 75, France" → linked to mv:Paris (ontology individual)
# "Toronto" (reviews) → linked to mv:Toronto (ontology individual)
# "New York" (reviews) → linked to mv:NewYorkCity (ontology individual)
# "Irving Plaza" (reviews) → linked to mv:IrvingPlaza (ontology individual)
# "Brooklyn, NY" → minted as new city (borough vs. city ambiguity noted)

# "The Fillmore Philadelphia" and "The Fillmore Silver Spring" are
#   distinct venues in the Live Nation "Fillmore" family. They are NOT
#   the same entity as mv:TheFillmore (San Francisco). Separate URIs minted.

# "Ziggo Dome" and "Ziggo Dome Club" appear co-located but are listed
#   as separate Ticketmaster venues; treated as distinct entities.

# "History - Toronto" (from reviews): resolved to venue:history-toronto.
#   Ambiguous name — flagged for human review.

# ==============================================================================
# GAPS — things the text describes but the ontology cannot represent
# ==============================================================================

# 1. ARTIST / PERFORMER — "Dave" (British rapper, full name David Orobosa
#    Omoregie, also known as "Santan Dave") is the performing artist for
#    every event. The ontology has no class for artists or performers.
#    Recommended addition: mv:Artist or mv:Performer with a property
#    mv:performedBy (domain mv:MusicEvent, range mv:Artist).

# 2. TOUR — "The Boy Who Played the Harp Tour" is a named concert tour
#    grouping multiple MusicEvents. The ontology has no Tour class.
#    Recommended addition: mv:Tour with mv:hasTourDate linking to mv:MusicEvent.

# 3. GENRE — "Hip-Hop/Rap" is listed as the artist's genre classification.
#    The ontology has no Genre class or property.

# 4. TICKET / PRICING — Presale status, ticket links, and add-on packages
#    (Fast Lane Access, Coat Check, Pre-Show Pass) are ticketing concepts
#    not representable in the current ontology.

# 5. COUNTRIES: Belgium and Netherlands — not present in the ontology as
#    individuals. Minted as new entities above; should be added to the
#    ontology's country roster with SKOS broader/narrower links to mv:Europe.

# 6. ADD-ON SERVICES vs AMENITIES — "Fast Lane Access", "Coat Check",
#    "Pre-Show Pass", "Rooftop Pre-Show Access" are ticketed add-on
#    services, not permanent venue amenities. The ontology's mv:Amenity
#    class does not cleanly distinguish between permanent facilities and
#    per-event purchasable services.
